## Summary

I've successfully added `VisualWidth` and `PadToWidth` functions to `pkg/display/` with comprehensive test coverage:

### Implementation Details

**`VisualWidth(s string) int`**
- Returns visual display width of a string
- Uses existing `StripANSI` function to remove ANSI codes (no reimplementation)
- Correctly counts Unicode runes (handles CJK, emoji, accented characters)

**`PadToWidth(s string, width int) string`**
- Right-pads string with spaces to reach target visual width
- Preserves ANSI codes (they don't count toward width)
- Returns unchanged if already at or wider than target

